**\n- Commented code blocks for step-by-step learning\n- Progressive examples from basic to advanced\n- Practical use cases and real-world applications\n\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Technologies Used\n\n### Frontend Technologies\n- **HTML5**: Semantic markup and accessibility\n- **CSS3**: Grid, Flexbox, custom properties, responsive design\n- **JavaScript ES6+**: Modern syntax, array methods, destructuring\n- **Web Fonts**: Google Fonts integration (Outfit, Fira Sans)\n\n### Development Practices\n- Mobile-first responsive design\n- Accessibility-first development\n- Progressive enhancement\n- Semantic HTML structure\n- Modern CSS methodologies\n- Clean, commented code for learning\n\n## \ud83d\ude80 Getting Started\n\n### Prerequisites\n- Modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)\n- Code editor (VS Code recommended)\n- Basic understanding of HTML/CSS/JavaScript\n\n### Running the Projects\n\n1. **CSS Grid Learning Module:**\n ```bash\n # Navigate to CSS Grid folder\n cd 01-CSS-Wizard-Foundation/01.1-CSS-Grid/\n # Open index.html in browser\n ```\n\n2. **Fungi Finders Website:**\n ```bash\n # Navigate to website folder\n cd 01-CSS-Wizard-Foundation/building-website-from-scratch/\n # Open index.html in browser\n ```\n\n3. **JavaScript Arrays & Objects:**\n ```bash\n # Navigate to JavaScript folder\n cd 02-JavaScript-Mastery/02.1-JavaScript-Basics/02.1.1-Arrays-Objects/\n # Open Index.html in browser and check console\n ```\n\n## \ud83d\udcda Learning Path\n\n### Beginner Track\n1. Start with CSS Grid fundamentals (`01.1-CSS-Grid/`)\n2. Experiment with different grid examples by uncommenting code blocks\n3. Move to JavaScript basics (`02.1.1-Arrays-Objects/`)\n4. Practice array methods in browser console\n\n### Intermediate Track\n1. Study the complete Fungi Finders website\n2. Analyze responsive design patterns\n3. Understand accessibility implementations\n4. Experiment with JavaScript interactions\n\n### Advanced Practice\n1. Modify existing layouts\n2. Add new 